<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 12:55PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Moore,
Montgomery, southern Randolph, east central Stanly and western
Chatham Counties through 145 PM EDT...
At 1255 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm
over Seagrove, or 7 miles south of the North Carolina Zoo, moving
northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Asheboro, Troy, Siler City, North Carolina Zoo, Biscoe, Seagrove,
Ramseur, Mount Gilead, Franklinville and Robbins.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
